&lt;p&gt;WE’RE HIRING! If you love data and are looking for unlimited growth opportunities, we want to talk with you about joining Further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further is a data, cloud, and AI company whose focus is helping companies turn raw data into the right decisions. We have an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gofurther.com/who-we-are&quot;&gt;award winning culture&lt;/a&gt; of extraordinary people. Our purpose is to enable people to thrive so that businesses can thrive. We believe that the work you do should matter - it should be meaningful to you professionally and personally, and it should have a positive impact on both you and our clients.&amp;nbsp; If this sounds exciting to you, let’s chat!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;ADOBE (AEP) ARCHITECT&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What experience should you have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+&amp;nbsp; years in enterprise data, MarTech, or digital architecture roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience within the Adobe Experience Platform, including one or more: RT-CDP, Journey Optimizer (AJO), Customer Journey Analytics (CJA), Web SDK.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with JSON structures, SQL (via AEP Query Service/Data Distiller), and REST APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level knowledge of XDM (Experience Data Model) and Identity Namespaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Adobe Experience Platform Web SDK (Alloy.js) and server-side data collection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading client discovery sessions, translating &quot;marketing speak&quot; into technical requirements, and presenting to executive stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nice to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in consultancy environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adobe certifications (RT-CDP, AJO, CJA).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of data privacy frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What you’ll be doing in this role:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will own the technical roadmap for AEP implementations, defining how data flows from ingestion (streaming/batch) to activation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You aren&#39;t just drawing boxes; you will lead the setup of schemas, datasets, identity stitching rules, and merge policies within the AEP interface.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architecting the frameworks for DULE (Data Usage Labeling &amp;amp; Enforcement), consent strings, and PII management to ensure compliant data usage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing the &quot;connective tissue&quot; between AEP and the broader stack, including Snowflake/Databricks, CRM systems (Salesforce/MS Dynamics), and advertising destinations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing the work of engineers and consultants to ensure implementation matches the architectural blueprint and Adobe best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What you&#39;ll need to accomplish in your first year:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the architectural design and oversee the successful &quot;Go-Live&quot; of at least two enterprise-scale AEP deployments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and document internal Further &quot;Playbooks&quot; for AEP schema design and identity resolution to streamline future client work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the go-to expert for complex troubleshooting, helping pods navigate difficult profile-stitching or data-latency issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gofurther.com/resources/total-rewards&quot;&gt;total rewards program&lt;/a&gt; is designed for your protection, peace of mind, and overall well-being. In addition to our outstanding basics, we offer a net-zero cost medical option, company contributions to your HSA, fertility support, fully-paid parental leave, a monthly stipend for your lifestyle spending account, and much more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply today or check out all our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gofurther.com/resources/join-the-team#current-openings-section&quot;&gt;opportunities&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
