&lt;p&gt;WE’RE HIRING! If you love data and are looking for unlimited growth opportunities, we want to talk with you about joining Further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further is a data, cloud, and AI company whose focus is helping companies turn raw data into the right decisions. We have an &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.gofurther.com/who-we-are/news&quot; target=&quot;_top&quot;&gt;award winning culture&lt;/a&gt; of extraordinary people. Our purpose is to enable people to thrive so that businesses can thrive. We believe that the work you do should matter - it should be meaningful to you professionally and personally, and it should have a positive impact on both you and our clients.&amp;nbsp; If this sounds exciting to you, let’s chat!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;AI Strategist&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rare opportunity to sit at the intersection of business strategy and cutting-edge AI, without being pigeonholed into either. You&#39;re not just advising on technology; you&#39;re shaping how major enterprise clients think about and invest in AI. From day one, you&#39;ll be working across a portfolio of marquee brands, helping them move from curiosity to confidence in their AI strategies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What makes this role unique is the scope of influence. You&#39;ll be the person in the room who listens to business stakeholders, translates their challenges into a clear vision, and then builds the roadmap that actually gets them there. You&#39;re the bridge: the one who makes sure AI investments deliver real, measurable value rather than becoming shelf-ware.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is also a role with staying power. AI strategy is still being defined across industries, and you&#39;d be helping to shape that definition, both externally with clients and internally.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What experience should you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10-15 years of experience in strategist or consulting role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep AI expertise, particularly in a consulting or agency role: ethical AI principles and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to articulate complex ideas simply and credibly, and create executive-level presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI / Machine Learning / advanced analytics experience in a highly-regulated industry (healthcare, finance, energy, defense).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in change management processes and a deep appreciation for its value in enterprise solution adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience driving adoption of Generative AI solutions in the enterprise&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus Points: AI governance certification preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll be doing in this role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead business development activities, including client pitches, creating plans and estimating work. This involves creating trusted partnerships to consistently extend and expand client relationships and engaging with CS and BD to develop new business.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify business outcomes and plan and delegate work to the team to positively impact them and communicate the a clear value proposition/story of our work to the clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Infer and communicate the consequences of new information/criteria/realities on specific client ecosystems or scenarios&lt;br&gt;Partners with senior clients to identify high-value AI opportunities, build strategic roadmaps for AI adoption, and establish governance mechanisms for AI programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide strategic direction to clients and internal teams. They lead major engagements, influence client decision-making and develop innovative approaches that create lasting value for clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focus, lead and mentor the teams to deliver measurable results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Frame AI work around testable hypotheses tied to real business outcomes (revenue, retention, efficiency).&amp;nbsp;&

